Polio Cases Reported in China’s Xinjiang Province, Xinhua Says

-- B y   C h r i s t i a n   S c h m o l l i n g e r
-- 
2011-08-28T07:19:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-28/polio-cases-reported-in-china-s-xinjiang-province-xinhua-says.html
Four infants in  China ’s Xinjiang
province were diagnosed with polio, Xinhua News Agency reported,
citing regional health officials.  The four babies range in age from four months to two years,
and are from Hotan prefecture, according to a press release from
the Xinjiang health department, as reported by Xinhua. The cases
were reported from July 3 to July 17.  Two of the patients have recovered and were released from
the hospital while the others remain in stable condition, said
the agency, citing the department.  The virus was confirmed to have spread from  Pakistan ,
Xinhua said, citing the Chinese Center for Disease Control and
Prevention.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christian Schmollinger in Singapore at 
